class Solution {
    public int bestClosingTime(String customers) {
        int n = customers.length();
        int totalY = 0;
        for (char c : customers.toCharArray()) {
            if (c == 'Y') totalY++;
        }
        int minPenalty = totalY;
        int bestJ = 0;
        int prefixN = 0;
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            if (customers.charAt(j) == 'N') {
                prefixN++;
            }
            int penalty = prefixN + (totalY - (j + 1 - prefixN));
            if (penalty < minPenalty) {
                minPenalty = penalty;
                bestJ = j + 1;
            }
        }
        return bestJ;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single left-to-right pass counts total 'Y's, then computes running prefix of 'N's and suffix of 'Y's to evaluate each closing hour in constant time, returning the earliest minimal-penalty index.

